## Under the hood

### The three-layer contract (Karpathy pattern)

- `raw/` — immutable. LLM read-only. One file per source document, provenance-stamped.
- `wiki/` — LLM-maintained. Curated, structured, wikilinked.
- `CLAUDE.md` — schema. Loaded every session. The contract.

Full details in [`CLAUDE.md`](./CLAUDE.md). Always read it before modifying anything under `wiki/`.

### Frontmatter

Every page carries YAML frontmatter with `type`, `title`, `date_created`, `date_modified`, `summary`, `status`, `tags`, `related`. Entity types (`person`, `company`, etc.) and synthesis types (`decision`, `meeting`, etc.) add their own required fields — see `CLAUDE.md`.

### Wikilinks

Cross-references use Obsidian `[[wikilinks]]` from the vault root (`[[entities/people/david-chen]]`), not markdown links. Every new page must be linked from at least one existing page.

### Deterministic capture, generative curation

The agent's capture hook is deterministic Python — not an LLM — so raw files land on disk reliably. LLMs only touch the curation layer (`wiki/`), where generative quality matters and errors are recoverable.

